in librational degrees of freedom of water in CTFs. We show that CTF-CN\nexhibits smaller surface area and water uptake due to a softer structure than\nCTF-2. The current study leads to new insights into the\nstructure-dynamics-property relationship of CTF photo-catalysts that pave the\nroad for a better understanding of the guest-host interaction at the basis of\nwater splitting applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 27 Jun 2020 13:26:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Feb 2021 11:05:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-24"}
